# Conventional commits

Every commit message MUST follow [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/) / Commitizen style:

```text
type(optional-scope): short imperative summary

optional body

optional footer
```

## Types

Use one of: `feat`, `fix`, `docs`, `style`, `refactor`, `perf`, `test`, `build`, `ci`, `chore`, `revert`.

## Rules

- Subject: imperative mood, no trailing period, ~72 chars or less
- Reference issues in the subject or footer when applicable (`(#17)` or `Closes #17`)
- Do not write free-form subjects like "Bootstrap a runnable…" — prefer `feat: bootstrap runnable Sapphire Botato (#17)`
- Prefer `pnpm exec cz` / Commitizen when a human is committing interactively; agents write the conventional message directly via HEREDOC

## Examples

```text
feat: bootstrap runnable Sapphire Botato (#17)
fix(music): reconnect voice on node resume
docs: document single-token concurrency
chore: ignore local pnpm store
```
